Drag and drop in Qt 4
http://doc.trolltech.com/4.2/porting4-dnd.html

In Qt 3, if I put an exception in the start_a_drag method, I have this.

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/wware/polosims/cad-qt3/src/TreeWidget.py", line 544, in contentsMouseMoveEvent
    self.drag_handler.mouseMoveEvent( event) #k worry about coords?
  File "/home/wware/polosims/cad-qt3/src/TreeWidget.py", line 147, in mouseMoveEvent
    self.start_a_drag(event)
  File "/home/wware/polosims/cad-qt3/src/TreeWidget.py", line 220, in start_a_drag
    raise Exception()
Exception

In the Qt 3 code, we have two kinds of drags: moves, and copies.


Here are all the event response methods for QTreeWidget.
